<HEADLINE> India Looking for Investment Opportunities in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Zambian government said its
strategic position between the Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) and the Southern African Development
countries (SADC) coupled with its liberalized economy gives it
great potential for investment opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Deputy Minister of Trade and Commerce, Jazzman
Chikwakwa, said this in Lusaka Wednesday when he addressed an
Indian delegation which is searching for investment opportunities
in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He assured them that they would not regret having invested in
Zambia as it had a great potential in tourism, agriculture and
mining.
</P>
<P>
He also said the government has adopted a liberalized economy
where it has left everything in the hands of the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chikwakwa praised India for being an all weather
friend adding that Zambia has benefited from India, economically,
socially and politically.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, India High Commissioner to Zambia, Ashok Attri,
described Zambia as one of his country's major trading partners
despite the information gap that has hampered a much faster growth
rate in their economic ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the investment from Indian companies in Zambia
during the period of 1994 to 1998 amounted to 307 million U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
