<HEADLINE> Tanzania Strives to Attract Asian Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 22 (Xinhua)-- Tanzania is expected to
launch a campaign to explore tourism market in Asian countries,
especially in South Korea, Japan and China.
</P>
<P>
The Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Natural Resources
and Tourism, Philemon Luhanjo, said here Wednesday that Tanzania
wants to start the campaign because there are a lot of people in
the countries.
</P>
<P>
"Hopefully this will increase our revenue when they come to
Tanzania," said Luhanjo, who will head an 11-member team to Asia
in late October.
</P>
<P>
Luhanjo's planned visit to Asia marks a new move of Tanzania to
explore overseas tourism market. The Minister of Natural Resources
and Tourism, Zakia Meghji, has been advertising Tanzania in Canada
and the United States over the past weeks.
</P>
<P>
The official said Tanzania plans to promote tourism to make it
the largest foreign exchange earner in the next millenium.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, six South Korean broadcasters are in Tanzania to
film scenic spots for their television stations. They left Dar es
Salaam Wednesday for the Spice Island of Zanzibar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
