<HEADLINE> 11th Babylon International Festival Opens in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The 11th Babylon
International Festival opened Wednesday evening in Iraq's
historic city of Babylon with the attendance of some 5,000 Iraqis
and foreign diplomats and artists.
</P>
<P>
Present at the opening ceremony were Iraqi Vice President Taha
Yassin Ramadhan, National Assembly Chairman Saadoun Hamaadi and
Deputy Prime Minister Mohammad Hamza Al-Zubaidi and several
ministers.
</P>
<P>
International troupes from some 50 foreign countries will
present folk music, dance and acrobatic performances in the 10-day
festival.
</P>
<P>
The Babylon International Festival, which started in 1987, has
been held annually except in 1990-1991 during which the Gulf War
broke out.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Minister of Information and Culture Humam Abd Al-Khaliq
told reporters that "Babylon will remain a distinctive feature of
Iraq's civilization which dates back to 9,000 years." 
</P>
</TEXT>
