<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Welcomes Saudi Arabia Statement on Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Wednesday welcomed
assurances from Saudi Arabia that the Arab country "is not one of
the states financing armed Chechen groups."
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia "follows a firm political line dictated by the
Muslim religion, seeks stability between peoples and countries and
does not interfere in the internal affairs of other states," the
Russian Foreign Ministry quoted a statement published Tuesday in
Riyadh as saying.
</P>
<P>
"These statements, which express the official position of
Riyadh, have been received with satisfaction in Moscow," the
Interfax news agency quoted the Foreign Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia is ready for "interaction with Saudi Arabia in fighting
terrorism and extremism" under an agreement reached during a visit
to Moscow by Saudi Foreign Minister Saud al-Faisal in March of
this year, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
