<HEADLINE> U.S. Arrests 93 in Mexican Drug Cartel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The United States said on
Wednesday it has arrested 93 people in a crackdown on one of the
largest drug cartels in Mexico, seized nearly 20 million U.S.
dollars and seven million U.S. dollars in assets.
</P>
<P>
The two-year investigation, dubbed "Operation Impunity," was
conducted by the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI), Drug
enforcement Administration and Customs Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The Associated Press (AP) said key to the success was
apprehension of three alleged "cell heads" working for the drug
trafficking organization that remained after the death of Amado
Carillo Fuentes.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement, Attorney General Janet Reno said,"The
impact of Operation Impunity is significant."
</P>
<P>
"By targeting the cartel's importation, transportation and
distribution network we have substantially hindered their ability
to move cocaine and other drugs into and around this country,"
Reno added.  
</P>
