<HEADLINE> Ba Gets Four-game Ban on TV Footage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 22 (Xinhua) -- French winger Ibrahim Ba has
been handed a four-game ban on Wednesday after the TV footage of a
Seria A soccer match showed him head-butting an opponent during a
Serie A match.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time the league has disciplined a player based
only on evidence from replays.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's Perugia 3-0 victory over Cagliari, neither the
referee nor the linesmen called the player to task for his attack
on Fabio Macellari. 
</P>
</TEXT>
