<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Becomes Greece's Biggest Trade Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Germany has become Greece's
biggest trade partner with the bilateral trade totaling 5.2
billion ecus last year.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian Press Agency (MPA) quoted northern Greece's
industries union as saying Wednesday that in the last five years,
German imports from Greece increased 20 percent, or an annual
average rate of 5.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last year, German exports to Greece stood at 3.56 billion ecus
while Greece's exports to Germany amounted to 1.676 billion ecus.
</P>
<P>
Greece's exports products were clothing, knitwear and
foodstuffs, and German exports were mainly machinery, chemicals,
plastics and vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, for the first quarter of 1999, Greece's exports to
Georgia amounted to 4 billion U.S. dollars while bilateral trade
constituted 2.3 percent of the country's foreign trade volume.
</P>
</TEXT>
