<HEADLINE> China Safeguards Sovereignty and Territorial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan Wednesday said that "the Chinese Government
and people will, as always, resolutely safeguard China's
sovereignty and territorial integrity, and continue to advance the
great cause of national reunification."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister made the statement as he took the
floor at the general debate of the 54th General Assembly session,
which began Monday.
</P>
<P>
"It is a fact universally recognized by the international
community that there is only one China in the world, that Taiwan
is an inalienable part of Chinese territory and that the
Government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate government representing the whole of China," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China's territory and sovereignty are absolutely indivisible,"
he said. "To realize the ultimate reunification of the motherland
represents the common aspiration and firm resolve of all the
Chinese people, including the Taiwan compatriots, and no force can
hold them back."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Government will continue to adhere to the set
policy for settlement of the Taiwan question," he said. "We are
firmly opposed to any attempt to create 'Taiwan independence,'
'two Chinas', or 'one China, one Taiwan'," he said.
</P>
<P>
"All moves to split the motherland are doomed to failure," he
said. "China's great cause of national reunification must be
accomplished and will surely be accomplished." 
</P>
</TEXT>
