abandonment of the political scene of Chile "has not been
touched," with Cook he said.
</P>
<P>
According to a Chilean newspaper, authorities from the Foreign
Ministry and the Presidency said that the government would
negotiate Pinochet's liberty with London.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was detained in October of last year in London, at the
request of a Spanish judge, who applied for his extradition, to
put him on trial for crimes against humanity during his military
regime, which was from 1973 to 1990. 
