was killed by unknown perpetrators and five rebels died in an
encounter with police Wednesday during a wave of violence in
Colombia.
</P>
<P>
President of the Union of the Ingenio Risaralda Hernando Mora
was killed by gunshots in his house by two gunmen in the locality
of La Virginia in the province of Risaralda, said the local
police.
</P>
<P>
Mora is the third union leader to be assassinated in Colombia
so far this year.
</P>
<P>
About the encounter between rebels and police, the police said
that the incident happened in the locality of Pie de Cuesta in the
province of Santander while the insurgents were transporting a
kidnapped farmer in the boot of a car.
</P>
<P>
Five of the rebels were killed and a further three fled the
scene, confirmed the police, who identified the kidnapped farmer
as Serbio Rey Mantilla.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five interconnection towers for electricity were
demolished in the last few hours by the guerrilla group, the
National Liberation Army (ELN), in the province of Antioquia in
the northeast of the country, said the authorities Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The towers damaged by the dynamite blasts are connected with
the Hydro-electric Center of San Carlos. 
