KUWAIT CITY -- Saudi Arabia said on Wednesday it will support
any possible Arab League boycott of the U.S. entertainment giant
Walt Disney Corporation over an exhibition dispute.
</P>
<P>
One of Disney's exhibit in the millennium exhibition, due to
open on September 30 at the company's Epcot Center in Orlando,
Florida, depicts Jerusalem as Israel's capital, which has become
the center of a row between Disney and Arab-Islamic countries
recently. (BC-Saudi-Boycott-Disney)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A senior member of the Democratic Front for the
Liberation of Palestine (DFLP), a Palestinian hard-line faction,
said Wednesday the DFLP has decided to join the peace talks with
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Taysir Khaled, member of the DFLP political bureau, said the
group made the decision after its leader Nayyef Hawatmeh met
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat in Cairo, Egypt recently.
</P>
<P>
DFLP's decision to take part in the peace talks reflects
efforts made by Arafat to rally more support from Palestinian
factions in peace negotiations with Israel, beyond his own Fatah
movement. (BC-Israel-Talks)
</P>
<P>
