Germany's Dax index fell 0.5 percent in thin trade on Wednesday
as the market failed to shake fears that interest rates could soon
rise in the U.S. and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Market sentiment had been dampened further on Tuesday when
Germany's Ifo business climate index jumped to a 12-month high in
August, auguring a possible interest rate rise in Europe.
</P>
