<HEADLINE> ADB Grants Loan to Boost Thailand's Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank on
Thursday agreed to grant a loan of 300 million U.S. dollars to
Thailand in a bid to promote the nation's agricultural
productivity.
</P>
<P>
In a news release available late Thursday night, ADB said the
loan is aimed to encourage Thailand to conduct structural reform
in the agricultural sector, which the ADB believes is needed to
remove the sector's weaknesses.
</P>
