<HEADLINE> U.S. United Technologies to Cut 14,500 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 23 (Xinhua) -- United Technologies Corp.,
a maker of aerospace and high-tech products, plans to eliminate
14,500 jobs worldwide over the next three years, or 10 percent of
its workforce, due to a downturn in the aerospace industry.
</P>
<P>
The products manufactured by UTC includes Pratt &AMP; Whitney jet
engines and Sikorsky helicopters.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several weeks, several UTC divisions announced
plans to eliminate nearly 5,400 jobs and consolidate or close
factories, according to the Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting Wednesday with investors, UTC chairman and chief
executive George David said about 9,100 more cuts are needed.
</P>
<P>
Most of the jobs to be cut will come from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The cuts will be made at such divisions as jet-control
manufacturer Hamilton Sundstand; Sikorsky Aircraft; Carrier Corp.
air conditioning; and Otis Elevator. 
</P>
