<DOCNO> XIE19990923.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Win Group at Asian Women's Volleyball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women spikers
met little problems in disposing of Australia 3-0, topping the
group with a perfect record at the Asian Women's Volleyball
Championship here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the one-sided game, the Chinese team, who won the tournament
six times in a row, enjoyed a great advantage in blocking, serving
and attacking over their Australian opponents, winning the 50-
minute match comfortably with a 25-11, 25-15 and 25-15 score.
</P>
<P>
"I think my team was working normally in the past five days,
but I must confess the team is still young and lacks experience,"
said Chinese head coach Hu Jin.
</P>
<P>
Foreseeing the round-robin finals, Hu said that China should
pay more attention to Thailand who had improved much in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
But he noted that China and Japan were long-time rivals and
they knew each other very well.
</P>
<P>
He said: "China will try their best to spike Japan and win the
tournament."
</P>
<P>
The top two finishers from each group will sail into the round
robin finals which start on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
China, with four straight wins against no loss in Group B, will
meet Thailand on Saturday while South Korea take on Japan.
</P>
<P>
In other Thursday action, Uzbekistan, ranked sixth in last
tournament in 1997, defeated Kazahkstan 3-1.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, beaten by favorites China on Wednesday in full
sets, followed China in Group B with three wins and one loss while
Uzbekistan, Australia and Kazahkstan, all with a record of one win
and three losses, ranked third to fifth in the group.
</P>
<P>
Early on Wednesday, Japan topped Group A with three wins and
Thailand finished second with two wins and one loss. Chinese
Taipei, who ranked fourth in the last event, got the third
position with one win and two losses while Hong Kong, China, came
fourth with three losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
