<HEADLINE> China's Social Scientists Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- One hundred and fiftyone
best research projects sponsored by China's National Social
Sciences Fund received awards today at a grand ceremony attended
by Chinese leaders Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
The projects were carried out between 1981 and 1995 and mainly
focus on major theoretical and practical issues concerning China's
reform and opening up to the outside world and its socialist
modernization.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was organized by the Publicity Department of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and the National
Philosophy and Social Sciences Planning and Leading Group.
</P>
<P>
Noted Chinese social scientists Fei Xiaotong and Lei Jieqiong
were given special honorary prizes for their distinguished
contributions to China's social sciences.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao said China's social scientific
research has been very vigorous and successful in the last 20
years, and that social scientists have made important
contributions to theories concerning the preliminary stage of
socialism, the reform and opening up, the socialist market economy,
the socialist democracy and many other areas.
</P>
<P>
Hu encouraged the social scientists to come to the frontline of
China's reform and construction drive, where they can find
solutions to major issues arising from China's reform and
modernization practice.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that freedom and democracy are important components
of scientific research and are vital in the search for truth.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president called on government and party officials at
various levels to fully recognize the importance of social
sciences and give full support to the work of social scientists.
</P>
</TEXT>
