<HEADLINE> Singapore Share Prices Close Nearly Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed nearly
unchanged on the Singapore Stock Market Thursday as the benchmark
Straits Times Index (STI) inched up 0.74 points to end at
2,068.40.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 159.98 million units valued at 376.41
million Singapore dollars (220.12 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
outnumbered losers by 190 to 78 with 182 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AsianMicro still led the volume list with 24.16 million units
changing hands. Gen Int came second with a turnover of 13.88
million shares. PCI was the next with a volume of 10.99 million
counters.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day rising by 110 cents to
close at 17.80 Singapore dollars. SembLog moved up 78 cents to
finish at 5.60 Singapore dollars. JurShip and Venture edged up 60
cents each to end at 8.05 and 15.00 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS, F&AMP;N and SIA led the descent of the day
losing 40 cents to close at 19.00, 5.90 and 16.60 Singapore
dollars respectively. SIA DBScw00 lost 30 cents to finish at 10.40
Singapore dollars. OUB sank 25 cents to end at 8.05 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Despite the overall moderate trading in the day, Creative
Technology shares surged on news it has entered into the Internet
service business with UK-based Cable &AMP; Wireless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
