<HEADLINE> Zhi Gong Party Sends Condolences to Taiwan Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The China Zhi Gong (Public
Interest) Party today expressed its concern for the huge losses of
life and property caused by the massive earthquake that hit Taiwan
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the Taiwan-based Alliance for the Reunification
of China, the party said that it is "deeply concerned and anxious"
about the heavy casualties and extensive property damage resulting
from the quake, and wishes to express its condolences to the
victims and sympathy to the compatriots that survived.
</P>
<P>
The letter went on to say that the disaster in Taiwan has
troubled all Chinese, especially when it occurred at the time of
the Mid-Autumn Festival, a traditional family-oriented holiday
celebrated by Chinese all over the world.
</P>
<P>
The party expressed the wish that the Taiwan compatriots will
recover from the tragedy and rebuild their homes as soon as
possible.  
</P>
</TEXT>
