<HEADLINE> Chinese American Socialist Activists in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 23 (Xinhua)-- Governor of Zhejiang Province
Chai Songyue met here today with Chinese American socialist
activists Anna Chan Chennault and Irving Kaufman.
</P>
<P>
Chai spoke highly of Chan's contribution to world peace,
especially to her effort to promote the cooperation between the
two sides across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Chan said she was greatly encouraged by the rapid economic
growth of Zhejiang Province as well as the whole of China, and
said she is willing to do more to aid the province's development.
</P>
<P>
Chan married Claire Lee Chennault, commander of the US 14th air
fleet, in 1947, and later became a naturalized U.S. citizen.
</P>
<P>
Kaufman is president of the SAT Corp. 
