<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Chamber Leaders Urge Canceling Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chamber leaders of Bangladesh
Thursday made an appeal to opposition political parties to cancel
their destructive programs of hartal (general strike) which they
said were seriously damaging the country's political stability and
economy.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement issued here Thursday, the chamber leaders
expressed their firm conviction that the government, the
opposition and all other concerned parties would reach consensus
to make their positive contribution towards ensuring the country's
overall socio-economic development.
</P>
<P>
The statement said opposition leader Begum Khaleda Zia in a
meeting with a chamber delegation on September 17 assured that the
opposition could shun hartal provided the government accept their
two demands of changing the chief election commissioner and
restructuring the Election Commission.
</P>
<P>
The chamber leaders expressed the hope that the government
would consider Begum Khaleda Zia's two demands as a positive step
towards restoring peace and stability in the greater interest of
the country's social, political and economic atmosphere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
