<HEADLINE> Chinese State Council Approves 2 Draft Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese State Council
today reviewed and approved the draft decree on minimum living
standards for urban residents.
</P>
<P>
It also reviewed and approved in principle the draft amendment
to the law on product quality.
</P>
<P>
The State Council made these decisions at its 21st executive
meeting, presided over by Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
The draft decree on minimum living standards will be
promulgated by the State Council after revision, while the
amendment to the law on product quality will be subject to further
amendment before it is submitted to the National People's Congress
Standing Committee for approval. 
