<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Chunyun, member of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC), met here today with a delegation of the Japanese
Democratic Party headed by Wataru Kubo, former deputy prime
minister of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), said that Chinese President
Jiang Zemin's visit to Japan last year and Japanese Prime Minister
Keizo Obuchi's trip to China this year have promoted Sino-Japanese
relations to a new stage at the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
He said that the China-Japan Joint Declaration on the
Establishment of Friendly and Cooperative Partnership Devoted to
Peace and Development is the guarantee of the Sino-Japanese
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Wataru Kubo said that China-Japan relations have developed
smoothly recently, adding "we will observe the principles of the
China-Japan Joint Statement and the China-Japan Peace and
Friendship Treaty."
</P>
<P>
He said, "we will continue to strengthen the good relations
between China and Japan based on a deep introspection of history."
</P>
<P>
The Japanese guests are here at the invitation of the
International Department of the CPC Central Committee. 
