<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State of Emergency in East Timor Revoked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie Thursday issued a decree, revoking the state of emergency
in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
State Secretary Muladi told reporters here that the government
decided to revoke the state of emergency because the situation in
East Timor is improving.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian military declared a state of emergency in East
Timor on September 7 in a bid to control the violence.
</P>
<P>
Violence began to escalate in East Timor after the United
Nations announced on September 4 that 78.5 percent of the voters
in the August 30 direct ballot rejected autonomy under Indonesia,
paving the way for independence.
</P>
<P>
The situation has improved since the U.N. multinational troops
landed in East Timor on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
