<DOCNO> XIE19990923.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemenis Go To Polls To Elect President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Yemenis went to the polls on
Thursday for the direct election of the president of the Yemeni
Republic for the first time in the country's modern history.
</P>
<P>
Under the supervision of observers, the Yemenis are to elect
one of the presidential candidates - the incumbent President Ali
Abdulla Saleh and the independent candidate Naguib Qahtan Al
Shaabi,
</P>
<P>
Saleh has been nominated by the national alliance grouping that
includes the "Yemeni Popular Congress, the Yemeni Union for
Reform, and the National Council for Opposition".
</P>
<P>
Election centers throughout the capital city of Sanaa are
witnessing a great flow of Yemeni men and women voters.
</P>
<P>
A Yemeni voter, called Abdul Qawi, told Xinhua that he was
"very happy today to exercise freely and without coercion his
right to elect the new president of the republic."
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that "the candidate I will cast my vote for
will fulfill the promises he has made in his election program."
</P>
<P>
Another Yemeni citizen, Ahmed Mohamed Yassin, said after
casting his vote in a Sanaa voting center, that "just like other
Yemeni citizens, I feel proud as a voter."
</P>
<P>
The population of Yemen amounts to about 17 million, which are
scattered among 19 governorates as well as the capital city of
Sanaa.
</P>
<P>
With regard to presidential elections, the Republic of Yemen is
considered one electoral constituency. But in case of
parliamentary elections, it is divided into 301 electoral
constituencies and 52 additional centers.
</P>
<P>
The number of registered voters stands at 5,600,117.
</P>
<P>
The number of supervision committees as well as the basic and
additional election committees throughout the country stand at
17,591, the total number of election boxes at 17,486, and the
total number of centers at 2,083.
</P>
<P>
Voting will come to an end at 6 p.m. on Thursday, and elections
results are expected to be announced on 27 September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
