<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's First Internet Portal in Hindi Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The world's first Internet
portal in Hindi was launched here Thursday by former Indian prime
minister I. K. Gujral.
</P>
<P>
The website was aimed at making the information super highway
accessible to millions of non-English speaking Indians.
</P>
<P>
The portal, promoted by the Indore-based Suvi Information
System and claimed to be the only one with contents in Hindi, will
have the latest news and features covering the world in general
and the Indian subcontinent in particular.
</P>
<P>
The portal also offers E-Yarta, a multilingual chat, E-Patra, a
free web-based multilingual service and extensive coverage on
sports, culture and cuisine.
</P>
<P>
Vinay Chhajlani, managing director of the Suvi Information
System, said, "We have already developed software which can send
E-mail message in Hindi, Marathi, Gujarati, Malayalam and Punjabi.
We are inviting relationships in developing portals in other
Indian languages as well." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
