<HEADLINE> China's Suzhou Has 11th Sister City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China's Suzhou City and the
Netherlands' Nijmegen have become sister cities, following the
signing of an agreement here today.
</P>
<P>
Nijmegen thus becomes the eleventh sister of the east Chinese
city in Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The mayor of Nijmegen, E.M.d'Hondt, and his Chinese counterpart,
Chen Deming, officially signed the agreement.
</P>
<P>
E.M.d'Hondt is leading a 22-member delegation from the city
government of Nijmegen which will attend an international economic
and trade fair in Suzhou on September 25.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou is famous for its long history, rich culture and scenic
gardens. The city has also experienced prosperous economic
development in recent years.
</P>
<P>
As the oldest town in the Netherlands, Nijmegen has many
historical relics and ancient buildings including the ruins of the
castle of Charlemagne. It is now one of the country's industrial
centers and a transportation hub.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
