<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Palestinian Legislative Council Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met
with a delegation of the Palestinian Legislative Council headed by
Speaker Ahmed Qurei here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li gave a high evaluation of Sino-Palestinian relations, saying
China and Palestine enjoy traditional friendship and the Chinese
people harbor deep friendly feelings toward the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in recent years cooperation in the political and
economic sectors have witnessed continuous progress, expressing
the conviction that with the advancement of the process of self-
rule and the founding of the Palestinian nation, bilateral
cooperation will have a broader future.
</P>
<P>
Li voiced pleasure over the Palestinian Legislative Council's
efforts to rule the country with democracy, adding that Qurei's
current visit has initiated a good beginning for friendship
between the council and the NPC.
</P>
<P>
On the situation in the Middle East and the peace talks between
Palestine and Israel, Li said China is closely following the
Middle East peace process, and welcomes the recent agreement
reached between the two sides on implementation of the Wye
Agreement and the resumption of negotiations on the final status
of Palestine.
</P>
<P>
This is another important step in the peace process, and also a
substantial achievement reaped through the flexible and practical
strategy of the Palestinian side, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed that China has consistently supported the
comprehensive, just and rational settlement of the Middle East
issue through peaceful negotiations, and that this is the right
and only choice.
</P>
<P>
China, as a permanent member of the UN Security Council and a
friend of Palestine, will, as always, support the just cause of
the Palestinian people in restoring their legitimate national
rights and interests, and is willing to work together with the
international community to strive for an early realization of
peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Qurei expressed congratulation on the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China, and said he highly
appreciates China's position on the Middle East issue.
</P>
<P>
Qurei is visiting China as Li's guest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
