<HEADLINE> Gold Steady, Silver Rises in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Silver prices rose further
sharply even as gold held steady Thursday on the bullion market in
Mumbai (Bombay).
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and 22-carat gold were quoted steady at the
previous close of 4,150 rupees (96.51 U.S. dollars) per ten grams
and 3,840 rupees (89.30 U.S. dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) rose smartly by 50
rupees (1.16 U.S. dollars) to close at 8,125 rupees (188.95 U.S.
dollars) per kilogram from the previous close of 8,075 rupees
(187.79 U.S. dollars) due to higher overseas advice.
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) improved further by 20 rupees (0.47
U.S. dollars) to 7,975 rupees (185.47 U.S. dollars) per kg from
7,955 rupees (185 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
