<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Chairman Meets Former UN Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met
with former Secretary-General of the United Nations Boutros
Boutros Ghali here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and the United Nations carried out good
cooperation when Ghali served as the UN Secretary-General.
</P>
<P>
China appreciated the valuable work done by Ghali for
safeguarding legitimate rights of developing countries, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Ghali said that in the past couple of days he witnessed the
great achievements made by China.
</P>
<P>
"China needs the world and the world also needs China," Ghali
said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the Chinese people are still faced with arduous
tasks on the road forward.
</P>
<P>
Ghali, incumbent secretary-general of the Francophone
Organization, introduced his organization to Li.
</P>
<P>
Ghali said his organization aims at maintaining and promoting
its culture, language and tradition, as well as pushing forward
the process of multi-polarization and peace and development in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China opposes the single-polar international
pattern and works to promote a multi-polarized world, which is
conducive to world peace.
</P>
<P>
Li also said China realizes that many efforts should be done in
pushing forward a multi-polarized world.
</P>
<P>
Li said he hopes the Francophone Organization will make new
contributions to world peace and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
