<HEADLINE> 22 Feared Drowned in Indian Boat Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 22 people were
feared drowned Thursday when a boat capsized in the Ganga in
Khagaria district of east India's Bihar state.
</P>
<P>
Local police said that the overcrowded boat carrying 26
passengers overturned after it was caught in an eddy while sailing
to Sultaganj from Agwani Ghat.
</P>
<P>
According to PTI, four passengers swam ashore while others were
reported to have drowned. Several buffaloes and cows being ferried
on the boat were also drowned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
