<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish Fashion Designer Apologizes for Erroneous Prophecy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Spanish fashion designer Paco
Rabanne has apologized for making a false prophecy that Paris
would be destroyed on August 11, the day of the solar eclipse, by
the descent of the Russian space station "Mir."
</P>
<P>
He told the French weekly "Paris Match," published on Thursday,
that he will always regret it. He said he has since been subjected
to numerous insults and abuses by the people of Annecy in eastern
France, which he calls his home.
</P>
<P>
Rabanne said that he was naive to believe the prophecies of a
self-claimed visionary in Bretagne, western France, and those of
Nostradamus, a 16th century French astrologist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
