<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Receives 250,000 Overseas Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China has received a total of
250,000 overseas students from 152 countries and regions since it
adopted the policy of reform and opening up to the outside world
two decades ago.
</P>
<P>
The figure was released here today by Ding Shisun, vice-
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress and president of the Western Returned Scholars
Association, at a reception marking China's National Day.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China has established a relationship of
educational exchange and cooperation with a total of 164 countries
and regions worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country has sent nearly 320,000 students abroad
to 103 countries and regions over the past 20 years. About 100,000
of them have completed their studies and returned to serve the
country.
</P>
<P>
"The returned scholars have contributed a lot to the social and
economic development of the country," he said. "Currently, many
Chinese students studying abroad have joined the 'Serving the
Motherland' program the WRSA launched recently to make China
strong through science and education."  
</P>
</TEXT>
