<HEADLINE> Malaysia Sets Up Committee for Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has set up a
Capital Market Strategic Committee (CMSC) to assist in the
development of a Capital Market Masterplan (CMP), the Securities
Commission (SC) announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The committee appointed by First Finance Minister Daim
Zainuddin will be chaired by SC Chairman Ali Abdul Kadir and
comprises six other members from the capital market industry, SC
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The CMP is a comprehensive plan which charts strategic
positioning and the future direction of the Malaysian capital
market for the next 10 years.
</P>
<P>
The plan also aims to address the weaknesses in the capital
market highlighted during the financial crisis, SC said, adding
that it would also provide a strategic road map to facilitate
future business development and assist in the creation of a
resilient and competitive capital market.
</P>
<P>
The CMSC is expected to present a report on the CMP to the
government within six months. 
</P>
