<P>
At the invitation of U.S. Trade Representative Charlene
Barshefsky, Shi will head a Chinese delegation to the U.S.,
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said at today's regular
press conference.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman noted that the U.S. has recently repeatedly
expressed its wish to resume negotiations with China on WTO entry,
and U.S. President Bill Clinton also formally asked Chinese
President Jiang Zemin to re-open the talks.
</P>
<P>
China and the U.S. resumed formal WTO negotiations following
the New Zealand summit between the two state leaders, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
WTO talks with the European Union are also expected to resume
soon, according to the spokeswoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
