contribution to the development of Sino-Singaporean ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral relations have been advancing smoothly
because there is no problem demanding a prompt solution between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The frequent contacts between the leaders of the two countries
will help enhance mutual understanding and trust between them, Zhu
added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is pleased to see that progress has been
made in bilateral economic cooperation and trade in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed his hope that the two countries will spare no
effort to push forward their two-way trade.
</P>
<P>
Lee agreed with Zhu's comments on bilateral relations, and
expressed his satisfaction with the development trend of bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that maintaining bilateral friendship is in the
interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong, Lee
invited Zhu to pay an official visit to Singapore. Zhu accepted
the invitation with pleasure.
</P>
<P>
Lee and his party arrived here Wednesday afternoon for a
working visit at the invitation of the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
Lee is also expected to attend the Fortune Global Forum in
Shanghai later this month. This is Lee's seventh visit to China
since he became Singapore's senior minister.  
