Among resource stocks, Rio put in a powerhouse performance,
racing 72.6 cents, or 2.84 percent, higher to 17.07 U.S. dollars.
Fellow diversified miner BHP added eight cents to 11.73 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 414.85 million stocks traded for 587.35
million U.S. dollars. Rising stocks outnumbered falling stocks 655
to 628 and 550 stocks remained steady. 
