contribution of parliaments to promoting and ensuring respect for
international humanitarian law on the occasion of the 50th
anniversary of the Geneva Conventions.
</P>
<P>
They will also talk about the need to revise the current global
financial and economic model, according to the IPU.
</P>
<P>
German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder, President of the
International Committee of the Red Cross Cornelio Sommaruga and
United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights Mary Robinson
have been invited to address the conference on October 11.
