<HEADLINE> China's Newest Tourist Guide Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China will implement
regulations on tourist guides October 1 and new tourist guide
certificates will be issued to replace the old ones.
</P>
<P>
These will be the second State regulations on the tourism
business. The first were Regulations on Managing Travel Agencies.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xiqin, deputy director of the China National Tourism
Administration, says that the regulations will help standardize
and improve tourist services and will play an important role in
protecting tourist legitimate rights.
</P>
<P>
He says that the old certificates will be null and void by the
end of the year. The new certificates, which will be used as of
October 1, have the name, sex, identity card no., language ability,
and travel agency of the bearer and validity date.
</P>
<P>
Tourist guide regulations say that all tourists guides must
have the certificate on them while they are working.
</P>
<P>
The Administration reports that China has more than 70,000
tourist guides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
