<HEADLINE> Loans to China's Largest Overseas-Funded Metallurgical Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Krupp Stainless
Co. Ltd., China's largest overseas-funded metallurgical producer,
has received 176.9 million U.S. dollars in loans.
</P>
<P>
These loans, 98.8 million dollars from the International
Finance Corp. and 78 million dollars from the German Bank of
Reconstruction and Development, will be used to finance the first
phase of a 1.4 billion U.S. dollar stainless-steel production
project.
</P>
<P>
The project, jointly sponsored by the Pudong Iron and Steel
Company in Shanghai and the world's largest stainless-steel
producer, Krupp Thyssen Stainless of Germany, will have an annual
production capacity of 440,000 tons of stainless-steel products.
</P>
<P>
China's imports of stainless steel will be reduced when this
project is completed.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project will cost 294.8 million dollars
and is expected to be operational by the end of 2001. 
</P>
</TEXT>
