<DOCNO> XIE19990923.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> University Receives American Scientific Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Central China University
of Science and Engineering has received a special scientific award
in the United States for its contribution to the development and
application of the Computer Integrated Manufacturing System (CIMS).
</P>
<P>
The University LEAD (Leadership and Excellence in Application
and Development) Award was presented on September 15 by the
American Society of Manufacturing Engineers (SME), an
authoritative academic and technological organization of the
international manufacturing industry.
</P>
<P>
The award, which was established in 1985, is presented each
year to a university which has made outstanding contributions to
the world's manufacturing industry. Qinghua University won the
award in 1994.
</P>
<P>
CIMS is a comprehensive technology which is used to improve the
competitiveness of manufacturing enterprises through the use of
information technology.
</P>
<P>
CIMS has played an important role in promoting the development
of manufacturing enterprises and the combination of production,
education and research, said Zhu Lilan, Minister of Science and
Technology, today. She said she hopes the university will strive
to win the Industry LEAD Award, another scientific prize given by
the SME, in near future.
</P>
<P>
CIMS is a key project of the State "863" high-technology
development program, which has involved 5,000 people from dozens
of colleges and institutes and 200 enterprises. Some 150
enterprises have introduced the CIMS to improve their
competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The Central China University has been listed among the top ten
premier universities and colleges in China for the past few years.
The university's CIMS center was built in 1989 and became one of
the major participants in the "863" project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
