<HEADLINE> China to Publish New Dictionary to Help Foreigners Learn Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 Xinhua) -- The Commercial Press
International Ltd., a joint venture of the Commercial Press in
Beijing, will soon publish a dictionary aimed at helping
foreigners learn Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The Xinhua Dictionary with English Translation, a bilingual
dictionary with both Chinese and English, is based on the Xinhua
Dictionary, 9th edition, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The first edition of the Xinhua Dictionary, the most widely used
dictionary in China, was published in 1957, and has been re-
printed over 100 times with combined copies of more than 300
million.
</P>
<P>
The new dictionary, which is also helpful for Chinese studying
English, will keep the full text of the Chinese Xinhua Dictionary,
which contains more than 11,000 words and 3,500 expressions.
</P>
<P>
The translation was done entirely by professionals, and the
final work will be examined and improved by other experts both at
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The dictionary is expected to be on the market by the end of
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
