<HEADLINE> Lee Kuan Yew: Earth-Shaking Changes in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Singaporean Senior
Minister Lee Kuan Yew said here today that earth-shaking changes
have taken place in China during the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Lee made the remark while delivering a speech on the
international situation and peace and development in east Asia at
the Party School of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China.
</P>
<P>
Lee arrived here on Wednesday, and used the expression "two
different Chinas" when comparing the country today to what it was
during his visit in 1976, especially the fundamental changes in
Chinese society and the rapid economic growth of the past years.
</P>
<P>
He analyzed the international situation after the Cold War,
elaborated his view on international relations and issues, and
said he looks forward to the prospect of peace and development in
East Asia and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 students and teachers heard Lee's speech. 
</P>
</TEXT>
