<HEADLINE> Cyprus Ready to Offer Financial Aid to Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus President Glafcos
Clerides has reiterated his country's readiness to offer financial
aid to Albania, the Cyprus News Agency (CNA) reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Clerides made the statement during a meeting with his Albanian
counterpart Rexhep Meidani in New York on Wednesday on the
sidelines of the U.N. General Assembly session.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents discussed bilateral relations, the Cyprus
issue and the situation in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Meidani told Clerides that the situation in Albania is now
stable.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also reviewed prospects for Cyprus' investments
in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Clerides briefed his Albanian counterpart on developments in
the Cyprus issue, and Meidani reiterated his country's view on
the issue which are based on the U.N. decisions.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were Cyprus Foreign Minister Ioannis
Kasoulides and his Albanian counterpart Pascal Milo, who extended
an invitation to Kasoulides to visit Albania.
</P>
<P>
The invitation was accepted and Kasoulides is expected to
pay a visit to Albania early next year. 
</P>
