<HEADLINE> Three African Countries to Hold Fair in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia, Malawi, Mozambique
trade exposition which takes place next month in Chipata, Eastern
Province of Zambia has attracted at least 140 exhibitors from the
three countries, Times of Zambia newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Eastern Chambers of Commerce and Industry
secretary, Norman Chipakupaku, as saying on Wednesday that the
exposition, the biggest of its kind so far, has attracted a large
number of exhibitors because of the inclusion of Mozambique for
the first time.
</P>
<P>
He said the three-day event is aimed at promoting the concept
of the economic growth triangle that is being supported by the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP), observing that this
concept could work successfully among the three countries because
of the vast potential in each state.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, which is scheduled for October 29 to 31, would
also be used to launch the Zambia, Malawi, Mozambique private
sector forum for promoting trade in the private sector between the
three countries, Chipakupaku said.
</P>
<P>
"The exposition will also serve to open the Tete Province of
Mozambique for business opportunities to Zambian and Malawian
businessmen," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
