<HEADLINE> Shanghai Major on Preparation for Fortune Forum (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is proud to be the
venue for the '99 Fortune Global Forum, Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi
said here today.
</P>
<P>
"This will be the last high-level international economic event
that Shanghai will host for this century," Xu said in an
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has turned from a processing, industrial city into a
multi-functional and modern international economic center over the
past 50 years, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
Since the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (
CPC) and the State Council decided to set up the Pudong New Areas
in the early 1990s, the city of Shanghai has recorded rapid,
sustained and healthy economic development.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has maintained an annual double-digit economic
growth since 1992. At present, its industrial output value
accounts for 12 percent of the national total, its revenue income
is nine percent of the national total, and its import and export
value is one-fifth of the national total, the mayor noted.
</P>
<P>
By 1998, the gross domestic product (GDP) of Shanghai totaled
368.8 billion yuan (44.4 billion US dollars), and the per-capita
GDP in the city exceeded 3,400 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"The tremendous changes in Shanghai are the epitome of China.
In my view, this is the main reason the forum chose the city in
which to discuss China's development in the next 50 years," Xu
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
