<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangyin Yangtze River Bridge Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The five-year construction of
the Jiangyin Yangtze River Bridge, which was completed recently,
has been approved following quality tests.
</P>
<P>
The 3,071-meter-long bridge at the lower reaches of the Yangtze
River has cost some 3.374 billion yuan (406 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
With a main span of 1,385 meters, it is the longest suspension
bridge in China and fourth-longest in the world. The bridge is 36.
9 meters wide and has six lanes designed for speeds of up to 100
km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The main arch span of the bridge is 50 meters high, allowing 50,
000-ton class cargo ships to pass through safely.
</P>
<P>
The sunken foundation is 96 meters long, 51 meters wide, and
reaches a depth of 58 meters underground, making it the world's
largest.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is an important section of two national highways,
the Beijing-Shanghai national highway and the highway between the
city of Tongjiang (in north China's Heilongjiang Province) and
Sanya scenic tropical city (in south China's Hainan island
province). It will contribute to the economic growth of Jiangsu
and neighboring provinces.
</P>
<P>
The 5,800-km-long Yangtze River is the longest river in Asia.
Since China started to build its first large-scale bridge across
the river in Wuhan in 1954, fifteen gigantic bridges have been
built over the river, a vital impetus for the development of the
country's transportation and economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
