<HEADLINE> Lao Currency Appreciates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Lao currency the kip
Wednesday went against the sliding tide of Southeast Asian
currencies by appreciating against the Thai baht to 145 kip per
baht or 5,800 kip per U.S. dollar, a 37-percent increase from last
Friday's rate.
</P>
<P>
The rate on last Friday was 254 kip per baht or 9,400 kip per
dollar, Thai newspaper the Nation reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An official at the Lao Embassy in Bangkok confirmed the
strengthening of the kip and said the appreciation of the currency
is the result of the Lao government's moves to manage the
plummeting kip which has taken a series of slides since the Asian
financial crisis broke out in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The official said the kip's value has been gradually
appreciating since last month. At the end of the August, the
exchange rate stood at 276 kip per baht. 
</P>
</TEXT>
