<HEADLINE> Helicopter With Four Aboard Missing in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter of Karnali Air
company of Nepal with one crew member and three passengers has
been missing since Wednesday evening, the Kathmandu Post reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The passengers aboard the helicopter with registration BK 117
include one British, one Canadian and one airline staff. It was on
a rescue mission headed towards Sunkosi River in Central Nepal.
</P>
<P>
According to Terminal Duty Officer at Kathmandu Airport Ram
Dines Lal Karna, the last radio contact was made at about 5:34
p.m. local time informing the tower that they would reach their
destination around 5:54 p.m. Since then nothing has been heard
from them and their whereabouts is still unknown.
</P>
<P>
The area where the helicopter was missing is about 150 km
southeast of Kathmandu.
</P>
<P>
Army personnel from nearby barracks have been dispatched to the
area in search of the missing craft, the newspaper said. 
