<HEADLINE> Chinese Peonies Exported to Northern Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Luoyang, a hometown of
peonies in central China's Henan Province, recently sent
additional 600 peonies to Finland and Denmark by air.
</P>
<P>
The Luoyang Peony Garden, the city's main grower, covers 10
hectares of ground and has more than 400 species, at least 110 of
which are rarities. It has sold over 200 species of peonies to
Japan, the United States, Denmark, and other countries in the past
few years, thanks to its exhibitions and gardens set up with
foreign cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The peony is China's national flower and Luoyang boasts a peony-
growing history of over 1,500 years and more than 800 species.
