<HEADLINE> Nepal-India Border to Close for Indian Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Nepali border officials of
Sarlahi, Mahottari and Rautahat districts and Indian border
officials from Sitamadhi district have decided to close
Nepal-India border area adjoining these districts during Indian
elections, The Kathmandu Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth phase of Lok Sabha (lower house of parliament)
election of India is scheduled to be held on October 3 in
Sitamadhi district.
</P>
<P>
The border will be closed on October 1, 2 and 3 in all the
three districts of Nepal, said Deputy Superintendent of Police
Surya Prasad Shrestha who attended a meeting of border officials
of the two countries on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Shrestha said it has been agreed at the meeting that from
September 28, alcohol and vehicles with Indian number plate will
be banned from entering Nepal, and massive patrolling will be held
in the border areas and suspicious people will be arrested.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, The Birgunj-Raxaul border route between Nepal and
India which accounts for 70 percent goods movement between the two
countries will remain closed for 48 hours from September 24 to the
morning of September 26 in view of the Lok Sabha election
scheduled for September 25 in that area, The Kathmandu Post said.
</P>
</TEXT>
