<HEADLINE> Lao Government Leaders Appreciate China's Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China's achievements in the
past 50 years presented as a miracle to the world. This is a view
shared by Lao government leaders including Prime Minister Sisavat
Keobounphan, Foreign Minister Somsawat Lengsavad and Minister and
Chief of the Government Office Saysomphone Phomvihan.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua recently in the Lao capital of
Vientiane, Prime Minister Sisavat said China's achievements in the
50 years show the advantages and vitality of socialism.
</P>
<P>
The founding of the People's Republic of China half a century
ago was a great victory after arduous struggle under the
leadership of the Communist Party of China, the prime minister
said.
</P>
<P>
"It ended the history of semi-colonialism and semi-feudalism in
China and enabled the Chinese people to be real masters of their
country," he said.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was making the remarks pending the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China on
October 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
During the past 50 years, Chinese people have built a backward
and poverty-stricken country into a powerful socialist state, the
prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
He was most impressed by the great changes in China in the past
20 years after China adopted the reform and opening-up policy.
</P>
<P>
"China has adopted the economic policy which conforms to the
real situation of the country and therefore its productive forces
improved rapidly," Sisavat said.
</P>
<P>
From 1979 to 1997, China's gross national product (GNP) were
increasing at an average annual rate of 9.8 percent, making the
country one of the fastest growing countries in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Saysomphone, an economist who is also president of the Lao-
Chinese Friendship Association, elaborated on China's economic
development in a separate interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"The reform and opening-up policy has brought the Chinese
people real benefits as their living standard has been greatly
improved," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that rural areas in China have seen significant changes
in these years.
</P>
<P>
He was also impressed by the special economic zones in China,
which enjoy favorable policies and therefore become very
attractive to foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
With the world's largest population of more than 1.2 billion,
China has accomplished what might take other countries scores of
years or even a century to achieve, he said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Somsawat also expressed his appreciation of
China's accomplishment in the diplomatic field, saying as one of
the five permanent members of the United Nations Security Council,
China has become more and more influential in the world.
</P>
<P>
"A powerful China is a very important element to ensure the
stability of the region and of the world at large," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed gratitude for China's keeping its promise of
not devaluating its currency in the face of the Asian financial
crisis, saying China's decision can only come from a strong sense
of responsibility for the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
