<HEADLINE> EU Urges All Parties of Congo to Implement Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In its declaration of September 1999, the EU acknowledged the
completion of the signing of the Lusaka agreement and expressed
its readiness to support the implementation of the agreement,
provided that all the parties themselves implement it in
accordance with its terms.
</P>
<P>
A Finnish presidential declaration released here today said the
EU expresses deep concerns over the delays in the implementation
of the agreement by the parties, the continued military activities
and hostile propaganda. The essential requirements for
implementing the agreement have not been fulfilled. For instance,
the selection of the representatives for the Joint Military
Commission has not been completed and the facilitator for the
national dialogue has not been agreed upon by all the parties .
</P>
<P>
"The EU therefore strongly urges all parties to fully abide by
the contents and the time-table of the agreement, which is the
negotiated instrument for a peaceful solution of the conflict.
The EU also encourages the UN and the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) to make all necessary efforts to support the
implementation of the agreement," the declaration said.
</P>
<P>
It also added that the EU will continue to support various
components in the implementation of the agreement, such as the
peace-keeping operations by the UN and the OAU, the Joint Military
Commission, the national dialogue, the reintegration of refugees
and displaced people in their countries of origin and the process
of democratization, re-habilitation and reconstruction in the
Democratic Republic of Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
