<HEADLINE> Indonesian Tourism on Road to Recovery: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian tourism is showing
signs of recovery despite the continuing monetary crisis and
political uncertainty, Director General of Tourism Gede Ardika has
said.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has shown significant growth in foreign exchange
earnings, as visitor arrivals from January to July 1999 totaled
2,237,928 compared to 2,019,052 during the first seven months of
1998 through 13 main gateways, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The political situation has created many changes to take the
nation along the path to democracy. In the tourism sector we have
a new paradigm in tourism promotion. We have changed direction
from a centralist to a de-centralist policy which has had the
effect of altering the position of our tourism image," he said.
</P>
<P>
For the tourism industry, it has meant the deregulation of the
licensing process, giving the provinces the authority to issue
permits for tourism development, Ardika was quoted by Thursday's
Indonesian Observer as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said that the industry is coming up with innovations,
offering a host of new packages at bargain prices, adding that
familiarization tours are being organized so that tour operators
and travel journalists can see the real situation in Indonesia, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
