<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Establishes Diplomatic Ties with Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar established diplomatic
relations with Belarus Wednesday at ambassadorial level, according
to a press communique issued by the Myanmar Foreign Ministry
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Belarus is the 82nd country in the world with which Myanmar has
established diplomatic ties since its independence in 1948.
</P>
<P>
Since 1988 when the present government came to power, Myanmar
has established ties with 14 more countries -- Peru, Venezuela,
Colombia, Papua New Guinea, Brunei, Brazil, South Africa, Kenya,
Kuwait, Ukraine, Azerbaijan, Georgia, Turkmenistan and Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The latter five countries were those that Myanmar forged links
in 1999 so far.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has opened 29 embassies, two permanent missions and two
consulates-general in various parts of the world, according to the
ministry. 
