<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Tighten Law Enforcement for Healthy Telecoms Equipment Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China's three central
government departments have decided to make joint efforts to
strengthen law enforcement on the country's telecoms equipment
market to see to it that there is healthy development of the
telecoms industry.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry (MII), State
Administration of Industry and Commerce, and State Bureau of
Quality and Technical Supervision held a tele-conference Wednesday
to make arrangements for the move that is expected to be launched
very soon.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the meeting, there will be a
nationwide check on commonly used products like telephones, mobile
phones, fax machines and modems.
</P>
<P>
The joint efforts will be focused on cracking down on bogus
telecoms equipment and unlicensed access to the telecoms network,
according to Zhou Deqiang, vice-minister of the information
industry.
</P>
<P>
To ensure healthy and secure telecoms operations, the MII has
stated clearly that telecoms equipment to be linked to the
telecoms network will have to be licensed by the Ministry and bear
a ministerial seal.
</P>
<P>
To crack down on illegal practices in the telecoms equipment
business, the three departments jointly released a notice about
increasing controls over the production and sales of telecoms
equipment in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
