<HEADLINE> Yugoslavian Official Unsatisfied with Kosovo Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A Yugoslavian official in
charge of Kosovo affairs Wednesday expressed his dissatisfaction
with the current Kosovo situation, though the Kosovo Liberation
Army (KLA) has been disbanded into Kosovo Protection Corps (KPC).
</P>
<P>
Zoran Andjelkovich, the President of Provisional Executive
Committee of Kosovo province said to UN side that the
transformation from KLA to KPC violated the UN resolution on
Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
During meeting with the representatives from UN delegation in
Pristina, capital of Kosovo, Zoran Andjelkovich said the
demilitarization of KLA has not been finished completely.
</P>
<P>
The present situation in Kosovo shows, the KLA has neither been
disarmed nor disbanded, it has just changed its name, Andjelkovich
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that UN delegation hasn't done its duty to carry out
its task given by UN Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The official demanded the UN delegation and international peace-
keeping force stationed in Kosovo to disarm the KLA completely.
</P>
<P>
The transformation from KLA to KPC was under the agreement made
on Monday by UN deputies in Kosovo and the KLA representatives in
Pristine.  
</P>
