<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru's Private Investment in Telecommunications Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Private investment in the
telecommunications sector has risen to 3.82 billion dollars, said
Pandolfi Arbulu, the Transport, Communication, Housing and
Construction Minister of Peru on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is optimistic about the prospects of
development in the sector after confirming that there is an
intention to invest 1.378 billion dollars in this field over the
1999-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the sector up to the year 2003 are to reach a
density of 21 lines for every 100 citizens in fixed and mobile
telephones, to widen the telephone coverage to 5,000 new populated
centers and to increase substantially access to internet, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said, "For the objectives, a minimum investment of 2.5
billion dollars is needed, that means an input of 1 billion
dollars over the 1999-2000 period." He added that now there are
plans to invest close to 1.38 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said that the number of installed telephone lines rose by
676,000 to 2.07 million and the lines actually in service rose by
673,000 to 1.64 million in the period from 1993 to the present.
</P>
</TEXT>
