<DOCNO> XIE19990923.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Economy falls in Second Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian
economy, submerged in its worst recession for over 50 years, fell
by 7.56 percent in the second quarter of the year, compared with
the same period of 1998, said the National Administrative
Department of Statistics (DANE) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The greatest contractions sections were farming (4.93 percent),
construction (24 percent), the manufacturing industry (17 percent)
and the financial institutions (7.03 percent), said DANE.
</P>
<P>
Coffee production, one of the principal export products of the
country, registered a contraction of 16.74 percent over the period
April-June, almost doubling that of the previous quarter of 8.04
percent, it added.
</P>
<P>
The international reserves, after months of stability, fell to
8.391 billion dollars in the quarter, compared with 8.7 billion
dollars at the end of 1998, while the unemployment rate reached
the unprecedented level of 19.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
DANE specified that the employed population dropped 2.17
percent in the second quarter, against the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian currency peso lost ground against the dollar,
with 1,641 trading for one dollar in April compared with 1,547 in
March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
