<HEADLINE> Food Consumption in Venezuela Slumps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's food consumption
fell by 10.6 percent in the first eight months of the year,
compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the study of the Datanalisis company published
Wednesday, the Venezuelan family income dropped by 5.5 percent in
the same period, which has limited the purchasing power.
</P>
<P>
However, the company forecast that by the end of 1999, the
consumption is expected to increase, since the price of oil, the
country's principal export, has been rising in the world market.
</P>
