<HEADLINE> CPV, CPJ to Further Strengthen Friendly Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The leaders of the Communist
Party of Vietnam (CPV) and the Communist Party of Japan (CPJ)
agreed to further strengthen friendly relations of the two parties
during their talks here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of CPV Le Kha Phieu had talks with Chairman
of the Presidium of CPJ Central Committee Tetsuzo Fuwa, who is on
an official friendship visit to Vietnam at the invitation of CPV,
according to local press Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the two party leaders had examined each
party's situation and discussed future activities to promote
bilateral relations between the two parties in line with the
promotion of cooperation between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Phieu congratulated the CPJ over its victory in the recent
elections, saying the CPJ has thus gained a very important
position in Japan.
</P>
<P>
He also welcomed Chairman Tetsuzo Fuwa's visit, which he said
contributed to the strengthening of the ties between the two
parties and the two nations.
</P>
<P>
The general secretary pledged that the CPV and the Vietnamese
people will always support CPJ in its struggle to improve people's
livelihoods and encourage social progress in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Tetsuzo congratulated Vietnam on the great achievements
recorded by its people during Doi Moi (renovation), saying that he
hoped the Vietnamese people would achieve more successes in their
desire to construct a modern industrial society.
</P>
<P>
Tetsuzo Fuwa and his delegation arrived in Ho Chi Minh City on
Monday, beginning a six-day official visit to Vietnam after ending
his visit to Malaysia and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Tetsuzo Fuwa, who is on tour of Southeast Asian countries, will
conclude his visit to Vietnam on Saturday. 
</P>
