<HEADLINE> Defending Champions to Compete in New York Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- John Kagwe of Kenya and
Franca Fiacconi of Italy, the men's and women's title winners last
year, will challenge several world class runners in the New York
City Marathon starting on November 7.
</P>
<P>
Allan Stenfeld, race director, announced their entries today.
Also competing in the race are 1995 world champion Martin Fiz of
Spain.
</P>
<P>
Kagwe, two times champion in the race, will try to become the
first person to win the event three consecutive years since
Alberto Salazar in 1980-82.
</P>
<P>
Fiacconi won the title last year with a time of 2:25:17, the
second fastest time ever for the race. She also finished second in
1996 and third in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Fiz won the 1996 Rotterdam Marathon and was eighth at the World
Championships this year. 
</P>
