<HEADLINE> Manchester United Back on Course in Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Reigning champions Manchester
United returned to the right course in defense of their title with
a 3-0 Champions League victory at Austria's Sturm Graz on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
United, who were held to a goalless home draw by Croatia Zagreb
in their opening game, now have four points but trail group D
leaders Olympique Marseille who won 2-1 in Croatia to move to a
maximum six.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona, who have failed to get past the group stage in the
last two seasons, look well placed this time after beating Italy's
Fiorentina 4-2 at the Nou Camp for their second win in group B.
</P>
<P>
Lazio came from behind to beat Dynamo Kiev 2-1 while Arsenal
scored twice in injury time to beat AIK Stockholm 3-1 at Wembley.
</P>
<P>
There were also wins for Germany's Bayer Leverkusen and
Borussia Dortmund while Norway's Rosenborg Trondheim drew 2-2 with
Dutch side Feyenoord.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United eased past Sturm, the Austrian double-winners,
without ever having to hit top gear.
</P>
<P>
Roy Keane, back after a month's injury absence, fired them
ahead with a 25 meter drive after 15 minutes and then two goals in
two minutes by Dwight Yorke and Andy Cole later in the half
settled it.
</P>
<P>
Marseille went ahead after five minutes in Zagreb when Ibrahima
Bakayoko scored but Tomo Sokota got a deserved equalizer in the
64th.
</P>
<P>
The hosts continued to press but Marseille grabbed the winner
with a great volley by Sebastien Perez 13 minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Barcelona were fortunate to beat AIK Stockholm 2-1
with two late goals but this time they struck early as Luis Figo
and Luis Enrique Martinez had them two up after 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Christian Amoroso pulled one back for Fiorentina five minutes
after halftime but two for Rivaldo settled it.
</P>
<P>
AIK suffered heartbreak for the second time in a week after
again being caught at the death.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal dominated the first half and led through their own
Swede Fredrik Ljungberg after 28 minutes but Krister Nordin
equalized for AIK six minutes after the break.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal continued to press and got their reward when Thierry
Henry scored in injury time and Davor Suker added a third.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona have six points to the four of Arsenal.
</P>
<P>
Lazio hit two goals in two minutes to beat Kiev in their group
A clash in Rome.
</P>
<P>
A Serhiy Rebrov penalty had the Ukrainians ahead after 67
minutes but Paolo Negro (69) and Marcelo Salas (71) turned things
round.
</P>
<P>
Lazio have four points, as do Bayer Leverkusen after the
Germans won 2-0 at Maribor Teatanic of Slovenia with late goals by
Boris Zivkovic and Ulf Kirsten..
</P>
<P>
Kiev, semifinalists last season, are still pointless after two
games.
</P>
<P>
Dortmund completed a good night for Germany as Fredi Bobic hit
two in the 3-1 home win over Boavista in group C.
</P>
<P>
Dortmund have four points, as do Rosenborg, who twice came from
behind to draw 2-2 with Feyenoord.
</P>
<P>
All four goals came in a hectic first 24 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Three of them came in a four minute spell as John Carew first
equalized Jon Dahl Tomasson's opening goal in the 21st minute and
then canceled out Brazilian Kalou's 22nd minute goal with another
equalizer two minutes later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
