<HEADLINE> Trinidad-Hoya Fight Sets Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The fight between Felix
Trinidad and Oscar De La Hoya set a record for a non-heavyweight
fight in HBO's pay-per-view telecast show with 1.25 million buys
and more than $64 million in revenue.
</P>
<P>
The previous record was 800,000 buys and $34 million from the
1997 fight between De La Hoya and Pernell Whitaker, according to
TVKO, the pay-per-view arm of HBO Sports.
</P>
<P>
Trinidad beat De La Hoya-Trinidad by one point in the 12-round
bout. The welterweight title bout ranks as the third-highest
grossing fight ever, just behind both of Evander Holyfield's win
over Mike Tyson. 
