<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, September 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said here Wednesday
that he believes France will play a role in the peace process
between Israel and Syria.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that France will play a role and will have an
influence of good will," said Barak after holding talks with
French President Jacques Chirac. (France-Israel-Barak)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton will meet Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat on Thursday and hear him about some new ideas
on the Middle East peace process, the White House said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Arafat requested to meet with the president to review some of
his latest ideas on moving the peace process forward," said Mike
Hammer, a spokesman for the White House national Security Council.
(US-Mideast-Arafat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Germany said Wednesday NATO's armed
intervention in Kosovo must not set a precedent for weakening the
UN's. role in dealing with humanitarian crises.
</P>
<P>
The move should not be a precedent to weaken the U.N. Security
Council's "monopoly" on authorizing the use of international force,
Foreign Minister Joschka Fischer told the 54th Session of the U.N.
General Assembly on the third day of its general debate. (UN-
Germany)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan
Wednesday held the ninth political dialogue with his counterparts
and representatives from the members of the Group of Rio and its
associated members.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Tang Jiaxuan said the Group of Rio, the
most important and widely represented regional political
organization in Latin America, has been playing a more and more
important role in international affairs. (UN-China-Group of Rio-
Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- An Italian navy transport ship weighed anchor Wednesday
night at the Italian central port of Livorno, bound for East Timor
with Folgore and Carabinieri paratroopers, vehicles and supplies
aboard.
</P>
<P>
Six hundred Italian soldiers will participate in the U.N.
mission in the ex-Portuguese colony, with a company of 200
parachute troops expected to arrive on the island before the end
of the month, the Italian Defense Ministry said earlier. (Italy-
Troops-East Timor)
</P>
