<HEADLINE> Pyongyang Acrobatic Troupe to Visit South Korea Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Pyongyang Acrobatic Troupe
from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) will visit
South Korea in November this year, a South Korean official said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Yoo Jae-bok, president of the South Korean Kyemyong Production
Co., told Xinhua that the 50-member Pyongyang troupe will hold a
total of 40 performances across South Korea between November 14
and December 14.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for the Pyongyang Acrobatic Troupe to
visit South Korea since the end of the Korean War in 1953.
</P>
<P>
Yoo said the South Korean government Wednesday endorsed his
invitation to the DPRK troupe, which is to enter South Korea
through the true village of Panmunjom.
</P>
<P>
Kyemyong reached an agreement last April with the Pyongyang
Acrobatic Troupe on the latter's performance tour of South Korea.
</P>
