<HEADLINE> Moreni Claims First Win for Liquigas on Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Christian Moreni took
the first win for his Liquigas team in this year's Tour of Spain
when he won the 225-km 17th stage between Bronchales and
Guadalajara on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Moreni finished a winning time of five hours 33 minutes 14
seconds after breaking away from a five-man leading group with
just four kilometers from the line.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Jose Garcia Acosta won the sprint for the second
placing, clocked two seconds behind Moreni, while Spain's Mikel
Zarrabeitia took third place and was given the same time as his
compatriot.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Jan Ullrich continued the race leader's golden jersey
after finishing more than 16 minutes behind the winner. 
