<HEADLINE> Egypt Beats Wales 3-0 for Squash Worlds Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Egypt won the title of the
World Team Squash Championship for the first time, storming over
Wales for a 3-0 victory here in Wednesday's finals.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Barada of the host played a thrilling five-round match
with Welshman Alex Gough. Barada led the first two rounds, but
Gough recovered to tie the third and fourth rounds. Barada ended
the set in the fifth round with a score of 9-6.
</P>
<P>
England edged Australia 2-1 for the third place.
</P>
<P>
Some 29 countries and regions took part in the tournament.
</P>
