<HEADLINE> Tang Jiaxuan Meets Counterparts From Rio Group Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan Wednesday held the ninth political dialogue
with his counterparts and representatives from the members of the
Group of Rio and its associated members.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Tang Jiaxuan said the Group of Rio, the
most important and widely represented regional political
organization in Latin America, has been playing a more and more
important role in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the Chinese government has attached great importance
to establishing and developing friendly and cooperative relations
with the countries of the Group of Rio, and the strengthening of
dialogue and cooperation between China and the Group of Rio,
mutual support, opposing hegemonism and power politics not only
help further develop relations between China and Latin America,
but also promote the position and the role of the developing
countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China is keen to develop closer, and more stable,
friendly cooperation with the Group of Rio with the efforts from
both sides.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that it is very important for the Group of Rio to
keep dialogues with China, Mexico's Foreign Minister Rosario Green
said the Group of Rio would further develop political, economic
and trade relations with China. 
</P>
