<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Jones Falls, Nasdaq Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks finished
mixed Wednesday with the blue chip index falling and the
technology stocks rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 74.40 at
10,524.07, adding to a 225.43 dropping Tuesday. The blue chip
index lost 801.97 points from its record closing high of 11,326.04
set on August 25.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's fall was mainly because investors were disappointed
at the weakening dollar. In the New York Foreign Exchange market,
the dollar continued to slide to 103.93 Wednesday from 104.87
Tuesday against the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
Among the companies leading the index lower were Union Carbide,
United Technologies, Procter &AMP; Gamble, Goodyear and IBM.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The technology
heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 37.06 at 2,858.16 and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 2.93 at 1,310.51.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq index was pushed higher by a number of technology
companies such as 3Com, Microsoft and Cisco Systems.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 0.17 at 601.16 and the Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 1.03 at 427.53. But the American Stock
Exchange index fell 2.53 at 782.45.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,711 down, 1,242 up and 578
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 808.23 million shares from 785.33
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
